{"title": "Summa Theologica - 10 Pars Secunda Secundae, Treatise on the Theological Virtues: Faith, Hope, Charity", "description": "The Summa Theologica (or the Summa Theologiae or simply the Summa, written 1265\u20131274) is the most famous work of Thomas Aquinas (c. 1225\u20131274) although it was never finished. It was intended as a manual for beginners and a compilation of all of the main theological teachings of that time. It summarizes the reasoning for almost all points of Christian theology in the West, which, before the Protestant Reformation, subsisted solely in the Roman Catholic Church. The Summa's topics follow a cycle: the existence of God, God's creation, Man, Man's purpose, Christ, the Sacraments, and back to God. (Summary adapted from the Wikipedia)<br><br>\n\nThis selection of the Summa Theologica covers questions 1-46 of the Secunda Secundae (\"Second-half of the Second Part\"), comprising a Treatise on the Theological Virtues: Faith (questions 1-16), Hope (questions 17-22), and Love (questions 23-46).", "duration": 97957, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1199", "name": "Saint Thomas Aquinas"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/summatheologica10_1509_librivox/summatheologicasecundasecundae_1509.jpg", "copyright_year": "0", "genres": ["Early Modern", "Christianity - Other"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "M.S.C. Lambert, LC"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "M.S.C. Lambert, LC"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Maria Therese"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Maria Therese"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Question 1 - OF FAITH (In Ten Articles), part 1", "readers": [9819], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/summatheologica10_1509_librivox/summa_theologica2_10_01_aquinas_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1905}, {"section": 2, "title": "Question 1 - OF FAITH (In Ten Articles), part 2", "readers": [9819], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/summatheologica10_1509_librivox/summa_theologica2_10_